Key Match Events: Trayce Jackson-Davis led the Warriors with 10 points against his former team
Stephen Curry returned to action after missing the last three games with a peroneal strain and scored eight points, including a buzzer-three-pointer to end the second quarter
Buddy Hield led the newfound 3-point duo with 10 points on 2-4 shooting from such a range
Jordan Poole finished the first half leading the Wizards with 14 points, two steals, and two blocks
Pre-Game Insights: Although the Wizards have made the game somewhat close, once Curry gets going, expect a blowout victory for the 5-1 Warriors
Others: The Golden State Warriors lead the Washington Wizards 54-45 after the first two quarters
Washington selected Jackson-Davis with the 57th overall pick in the 2023 NBA Draft
